    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add the <strong>black rice </strong>to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water </strong>and cook over a high heat for 30 min or until it's tender (it will still have a slight bite to it when cooked)</p><p>Once cooked, drain and return to the pot, then cover with a lid until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, deseed the <strong>red</strong> <strong>pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</strong> </span>(scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p><p>Peel (scrape the skin off with a teaspoon) and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>ginger</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with matching lid) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>pepper strips</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the pepper is cooking, chop the <strong>creamed coconut</strong> roughly (if required!)</p><p>Dissolve the <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong>, <strong>lime leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</span> </strong>and <strong>chopped creamed coconut</strong> in 150ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[250ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>coconut stock</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>basa fillets</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p><p>Crush the <strong>roasted</strong> <strong>peanuts</strong> in the bag with a <strong>rolling pin</strong></p><p>Wash the <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has softened, add the <strong>Thai red curry paste</strong>, <strong>chopped ginger</strong>,<strong> chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) to the pan and cook for 30 secs or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>coconut stock</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until the sauce has started to thicken</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once thickened, add the <strong>basa pieces</strong> and <strong>spinach</strong> to the pan</p><p>Cook, covered, for 4 min further or until the fish is cooked through and the spinach has wilted </p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked when it turns opaque and flakes easily</p><p>Once done, remove the <strong>lime leaf<span class=\"text-danger\">[ves]</strong> </span>and discard \u2013 this is your <strong>Thai red basa curry</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/thai-red-basa-curry-with-black-rice-and-roasted-peanuts/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>Thai red basa curry</strong> over the <strong>black rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with <strong>crushed</strong> <strong>roasted peanuts</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
